# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MATHBHOOT TOOLING DECISIONS (documentation only; reviewed 2026-07-20)
# Selection rule: free/open-source or a worthwhile free tier for current needs.
# These comments do not install tools or change Git ignore behavior.
#
# Core development:
# - VS Code: code editor
# - Codex; Gemini CLI optional: AI-assisted development and second opinions
# - Git + GitHub: version control, repository, issues, projects, and releases
# - HTML + modular CSS + vanilla JavaScript: primary frontend stack
# - External JSON + JSON Schema: game/content storage and validation
# - Vite + npm: local development and production builds (approval required)
# - ESLint + Prettier: code quality and formatting
#
# Backend, hosting, and delivery:
# - Supabase: PostgreSQL, Auth, RLS, Storage, Edge Functions, and SQL tests
# - Vercel: deployment while the project remains eligible for Hobby use
# - Cloudflare Pages: preferred free alternative for commercial deployment
# - Cloudflare DNS + Turnstile: DNS and bot protection
# - Resend: production authentication/transactional email when required
#
# Testing, security, and operations:
# - Vitest: JavaScript unit tests
# - Playwright + axe-core: browser, mobile, visual, and accessibility tests
# - Lighthouse/PageSpeed Insights: performance, accessibility, SEO, best practices
# - GitHub Actions + Dependabot: CI/CD and dependency updates
# - Gitleaks + npm audit + OWASP ZAP: secrets, dependencies, and staging security
# - Sentry: production error monitoring before public beta
# - UptimeRobot: availability monitoring before public beta
# - Cloudflare Web Analytics: basic privacy-friendly traffic analytics
# - PostHog: later, only for defined gameplay/product analytics questions
# - Bruno: API testing when Edge Functions or APIs are introduced
# - k6: load testing before a major public launch
#
# Interactive/game modules (use only when a feature justifies the overhead):
# - DOM/CSS/Web Animations API: default interaction and animation approach
# - GSAP free core: complex animation timelines
# - Phaser: substantial 2D game levels
# - Three.js: approved 3D rooms or boss levels
# - Matter.js: advanced 2D physics
# - KaTeX: substantial mathematical notation
#
# Free creative and content tools:
# - Penpot: UI/UX design and prototypes
# - Krita: digital painting and character art
# - Inkscape: SVG, icons, and vector art
# - Blender: 3D modelling and animation
# - Audacity: audio editing
# - Kdenlive: video editing
# - FFmpeg: audio/video conversion and optimization
# - Squoosh; Sharp later: manual and automated image optimization
# - OBS Studio: screen recording and trailers
# - Weblate/Crowdin: later, if collaborative localization is needed
#
# Deliberately not selected now:
# - React, Next.js, Vue, Tailwind CSS, Firebase, custom Node/Python backend
# - AWS S3, Docker/Podman/Kubernetes, Postman, Selenium, Trivy, or a CMS
# - Multiple overlapping analytics products running simultaneously
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
